snippet.textDisplay:
Wall of text warning!

It's funny, some of the things coronavirus is doing to everyone. In your case, you're having to make the hard, but responsible, decision of what needs to go for the benefit of your passion. In my own, I've spent more time on YouTube lately, and as a result, I've found some really interesting channels that I would never have had time for before(yours among them).

Firstly, your videos are outstanding. The camera work is phenomenal, the sound is very crisp and clear, the information is very good, and your optimism and passion is very clearly evident. You've converted me from someone who knows nothing about ant keeping to someone who is genuinely interested in starting a colony(after a bunch more research).

Secondly, my favourite of your collection would have to be the Phoenix Empire. Fire ants were always something that I considered to be a pest, and it wasn't until I started binging your videos that I found myself interested in their behaviours.

I have liked, subscribed, requested notifications, and look forward to news of the Phoenix Empire. Stay healthy.

snippet.textDisplay:
makes sense to release the ones who are endemic to the region. not only will they not upset the local eco, but they are used to the environment and have very good odds of survival.
To be fair, i've never been a fan of insects, the "nasty creepy crawlies", but somehow i always liked your vids, i do like watching nature like that and although i am not that much a fan of keeping insects, it was always fun to watch the vids.
things have been changing a bit though, although i don't particularly like insects, i do like my geckos and my new bearded dragon. so i am looking into breeding feeder insects myself. but luckily pet stores can still sell food and care products for pets in my region so they are still open and i don't need to rush into insect breeding for my lizardos ^^
anyways, just wanted to say, whatever happens, know that you're doing at least 'something' right, cause even though i personally dislike insects, i always enjoyed your vids ^^
and i'm sure i'll be enjoying the new antiverse adventures once the quarantine is over ^^
